ABUJA (Sundiata Post) Chief Justice of Nigeria, Justice Walter Onnoghen will on Monday face the Code of Conduct Tribunal on a 6 counts charge over allegations of Non declaration of assets. The news has left many Nigerians talking on social media. Recall that CJN Onnoghen’s confirmation was delayed and met with alot of protest before it eventually happened. There are insinuation that his current trial might have a relationship with next month’s presidential election and President Buhari’s agenda.     